# ğŸ“ School Management System (Java Project)

Below is the full project structure.
Each file is separated with a clear path.

---

## ğŸ“‚ src/school/Person.java
```java
package school;

public class Person {
    private String name;        // private â†’ only inside Person
    protected int age;          // protected â†’ subclasses + same package
    public String role;         // public â†’ anywhere

    public Person(String name, int age, String role) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
        this.role = role;
    }

    // Public wrapper method to access private variable
    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }

    private void secretInfo() {
        System.out.println("This is private information!");
    }

    public void showSecret() {
        secretInfo();  // wrapper for private method
    }
}
```

---

## ğŸ“‚ src/school/Student.java
```java
package school;

public class Student extends Person {

    protected String course;   // protected variable

    public Student(String name, int age, String course) {
        super(name, age, "Student");
        this.course = course;
    }

    public void display() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + getName());  // public wrapper â†’ OK
        System.out.println("Age: " + age);         // protected â†’ OK (same package)
        System.out.println("Course: " + course);
        System.out.println("Role: " + role);       // public â†’ OK
    }

    // Getter so Teacher or outside classes can access course
    public String getCourse() {
        return course;
    }
}
```

---

## ğŸ“‚ src/staff/Teacher.java
```java
package staff;

import school.Person;
import school.Student;

public class Teacher extends Person {

    public String subject;

    public Teacher(String name, int age, String subject) {
        super(name, age, "Teacher");
        this.subject = subject;
    }

    public void display() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + getName());            // âœ” public
        System.out.println("Age: " + age);                   // âœ” protected via inheritance
        System.out.println("Subject: " + subject);
        System.out.println("Role: " + role);
    }

    public void checkStudentCourse(Student s) {
        System.out.println("Student Course: " + s.getCourse());  // âœ” via public method
    }
}
```

---

## ğŸ“‚ src/school/MainApp.java
```java
package school;

import staff.Teacher;

public class MainApp {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Student s = new Student("Rahul", 20, "Computer Science");
        Teacher t = new Teacher("Mr. Sharma", 35, "Math");

        System.out.println("---- Student Info ----");
        s.display();

        System.out.println("\n---- Teacher Info ----");
        t.display();

        System.out.println("\n---- Teacher Checking Student Course ----");
        t.checkStudentCourse(s);  // using getter
    }
}
```

